paragraph.text:
require a consumer
				to pay interest and fees that, combined, total more than 15 cents for every
				dollar loaned in connection with a payday loan;

take or attempt to
				take an interest in any of the consumer’s personal property to secure the
				loan;

subparagraph.text:
a mandatory
				arbitration clause that is oppressive, unfair, unconscionable, or substantially
				in derogation of the rights of consumers;

paragraph.text:
knowingly accept
				payment in whole or in part for any obligation under an extended repayment plan
				based on funds obtained from another payday loan;

charge or attempt
				to collect, attorney’s fees, court costs, or arbitration costs incurred in
				connection with the collection of a payday loan;
